{"article_id":"jgGY80qh7pBVjLZg","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"New Jersey Gov . Chris Christie 's administration on Monday said","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"a health care worker","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"quarantined under an Ebola watch","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"after she returned from Sierra Leone","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"-- and who threatened a lawsuit --","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"has been cleared to go home .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"The state Department of Health said","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"the patient , Kaci Hickox , has been symptom-free for 24 hours ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"and `` is being discharged ''","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"after being evaluated in coordination with the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"The move comes","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"as New Jersey and New York have faced pressure from the Obama administration","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"to dial back their quarantine policies .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"New York Gov . Andrew Cuomo announced late Sunday","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"he had loosened some of the restrictions in a mandatory 21-day Ebola quarantine","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that he had ordered along with Christie this past Friday .","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"In New Jersey , Hickox , a nurse from Maine , blasted the state ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"she was treated `` like a criminal . ''","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"Hickox tested negative for Ebola in a preliminary evaluation ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"but Christie 's administration continued to stand by its policies .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"The health department said Monday","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that the patient was subject to quarantine at first","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"because she had direct exposure to people","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"suffering from Ebola in West Africa .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"At this point , though , she has requested to return to Maine ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and the state says","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"that will be arranged `` via a private carrier . ''","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"`` She will remain subject to New Jersey 's mandatory quarantine order while in New Jersey , ''","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"the department said .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"`` Health officials in Maine have been notified of her arrangements","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"and will make a determination under their own laws on her treatment","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"when she arrives . ''","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"The department also stressed","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"while in isolation ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"the nurse was given access to `` a computer , cell phone , reading material and nourishment of choice . ''","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"Christie issued a statement on Sunday","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"that stressed","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that home confinement would be used for New Jersey residents and others","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"when possible .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"`` The protocol is clear","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"that a New Jersey resident with no symptoms ,","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"but who has come into contact with someone with Ebola , such as a health care provider ,","depth":14},{"id":44,"text":"would be subject to a mandatory quarantine order","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"and quarantined at home .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"Non-residents would be transported to their homes","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"if feasible","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"and , if not , quarantined in New Jersey , ''","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"said a statement from Christie spokesman Kevin Roberts .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"But New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"calling Hickox a `` returning hero , ''","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"charged","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that she was `` treated with disrespect ''","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"when she was put into quarantine .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that she was interrogated repeatedly","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"and things were not explained well to her .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"Cuomo , too , took a softer tone","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"in issuing revised guidelines for his state on Sunday .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Under the new guidelines , medical professionals","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"who have had contact with Ebola patients","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"will be quarantined at home","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"and receive twice-daily monitoring","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"if they have no symptoms .","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"Family members will be allowed to stay ,","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"and friends may visit with the approval of health officials .","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"The state will also pay for any lost compensation ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"if they are not paid by a volunteer organization .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"The new guidelines come","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"after White House officials and health experts strongly criticized the mandatory quarantine ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"which was put in place in response to the infection of a New York City doctor , Craig Spencer .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"Cuomo had originally criticized Dr. Spencer","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"for not obeying a 21-day voluntary quarantine .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"But on Sunday , he called the health care workers `` heroes ''","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"and said","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"his administration would encourage more medical workers to volunteer","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"to fight Ebola .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"Meanwhile , in New York a 5-year-old boy","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"returning from West Africa","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"reportedly was taken to a local hospital Sunday with possible Ebola symptoms .","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"He was reported to have a 103-degree fever .","depth":4},{"id":82,"text":"Earlier Sunday the White House expressed concern about what it called the `` unintended consequences '' of the mandatory quarantine ,","depth":4},{"id":83,"text":"telling Fox News","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"that the Obama administration is working on new federal guidelines","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"on returning health-care workers","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"exposed to Ebola ,","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"realizing the concern among Americans about a potential outbreak on U.S. soil .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"Dr. Anthony Fauci , director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases , said early Sunday","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"that the 21-day quarantines","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"originally imposed in Florida , Illinois , New Jersey , and New York","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"can have the `` unintended consequence ''","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"of discouraging health care workers from volunteering , particularly in the West African countries ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"where an estimated 4,500 people have so far this year died from Ebola .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"`` We do not want to put them in a position","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"where it makes it very , very uncomfortable for them to even volunteer , ''","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"he told \" Fox News Sunday . ''","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"Christie told Fox News","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"that he has \" great respect \" for Fauci","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"but defended his decision","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"to impose the quarantine ,","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"he has an obligation","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"to protect residents amid Centers for Disease Control guidelines","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"that remain a \" moving target . \"","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"`` Imagine","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"that you 're the person in charge of public health for people of a large , densely populated state ...","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"and these protocols continue to move and change , \"","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"Christie said .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"\" It was my conclusion","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"we need to do this","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"to protect the public health of people of New Jersey .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"( New York ) Governor Cuomo agreed .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"And now , ( Chicago ) Mayor Emanuel agrees .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"And I think","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"the CDC eventually will come around to our point of view on this . ''","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Officials at New York City 's Bellevue Hospital Center said Sunday","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"that Spencer was in serious but stable condition ,","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"was looking better","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"than he did the day before ,","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"and tolerated a plasma treatment well .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"The World Health Organization said","depth":2},{"id":122,"text":"more than 10,000 people have been infected with Ebola in the outbreak","depth":4},{"id":123,"text":"that came to light last March ,","depth":4},{"id":124,"text":"and nearly half of them have died , mostly in Guinea , Sierra Leone and Liberia .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":249,"left":245,"right":248,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":206,"right":244,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":202,"right":205,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":134,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":130,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":0,"right":129,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":129,"left":128,"right":5,"rel